authorMeta.name: saasgod
text:
Starting a SaaS business doesn‚Äôt come easy. Failure happens more often than success but if you are persistent through failures and actually ship/market your product the pay off can be massive. Thousands of solo entrepreneurs have built SaaS and never have to work again. A solid subscriber base can change your life forever.

The start of my first business was a grueling yet enlightening 9 months. I had underestimated the breadth of roles one has to assume. There was a massive wakeup call and  disappointment when my initial SaaS product, despite having 2000 beta subscribers, failed to convert a single a paying customer on its debut. I took action and changed my pricing model after understanding the needs of my customer and their relationship with our competitors.
